bio.experienceSummary: Hi, I'm Zanielle! As a fun-loving babysitter with a knack for cooking, arts and crafts, and tutoring, I'm here to ensure your kids have a blast while you're away. With a reliable car, I can safely transport them to activities. Working from home as an IT project manager, I bring organization and dependability to my babysitting. Let's cook, create, and learn together for memorable experiences!

Hi! My name is Catie, I am 25 years old. I am currently a teacher looking for some after school or weekend hours with your family! I have my masters degree in elementary and special education, so am available for both babysitting and/or tutoring. I have worked with children for over 10 years, and have experience with infants to middle schoolers. I am hard working and reliable and am so excited to hear from you and become a part of the family!

With 15 years of experience as a professional nanny and household manager, I have supported children through all developmental stages, from infancy to adolescence, while providing seamless household management for busy families. I specialize in newborn care, developmental milestones, and managing challenging behaviors, creating a nurturing environment that encourages growth, independence, and creativity. In my most recent role, I provided comprehensive care for three children, overseeing daily routines, meal preparation, educational support, and enrichment activities. My experience extends beyond childcare to include household operations, logistics coordination, and family travel planning, ensuring every detail is managed with efficiency and care. My approach is grounded in fostering strong communication with parents, maintaining a transparent and collaborative environment that prioritizes the well-being and development of each child.

description.displayText:
How can I even begin to describe to you just how incredible Samantha is? I guess I will have to start from the beginning! My husband and I interviewed Samantha a few months before our daughter was born.  From the very first meeting we were impressed with her intelligence, certifications and experience. We knew we had met someone very special and needed to hire her right away!  During my maternity leave, Samantha visited often to get to know us and our baby.  This truly helped with my return to work.

Samantha has been with our family for two years and I can say with confidence, that Samantha has made the utmost impact on our daughter and is part of our family. The love, attention she has given our daughter goes far beyond caring for basic needs.  She nurtures her, guides her and sets examples and boundaries to help her grow.  While we know it is the right time for our daughter to go to school, we will miss Samantha terribly! You and your child will be so lucky to have her!

bio.experienceSummary: I'm a mother of 2 boys. My oldest child have autism as well as my youngest brother who is over 20 years old. I've been great with kids since 2003 and work in summer camps for the city of Elizabeth and watched other children with /without special needs

Hi! My name is Adriana :) I've been a sitter throughout high school, college, and over the past few years. I was a lifeguard for 10 years, as well as a certified EMT for 8, which ensures my ability to maintain vigilance and always be prepared to manage any situation that presents itself. Your child's safety and comfort is my priority. In addition, I am responsible, caring, and love spending time with kids! Please don't hesitate to ask any questions. Messages welcome! :)

description.displayText: Adriana was great each time our family hired her to babysit. She's great with kids and always has something up her sleeve to pull out when the kids can't figure out what to do. She always showed up a few minutes early and asked questions about the kids to make sure she had any extra details she needed to ensure they were all taken care of in case anything came up.

bio.experienceSummary: Hello, everyone! My name is Steph. I grew up in Trenton NJ but have seen many parts of the world thanks to the great families I had the opportunity to work with. Honestly I had an affinity for children at a early age. I loved babysitting my nieces and nephews when I was a teen, especially during the summer. I'm proud to say that this made me realize later in life that I enjoy working with juveniles. Nannying influenced my career choice for school which is a duel major in early childhood education and law enforcement. Thanks to my schooling and experience with all ages I can always invent creative and fun games. I find that children have always connected to my personality and my exciting spirit. I love being a nanny; it is the most rewarding and fulfilling job out there. Children are a delightful gift: they bring so much joy to my heart and make everyday so much better.

description.displayText: Stephanie has worked for me for about 3 months now.  She helps me with my 3.5 year old and 8 month old.  She plays with the kids and does anything else I ask her to such has dishes and laundry.  I wouldn't hesitate to hire Stephanie.

bio.experienceSummary:
Hello! I'm Tatyana, a dedicated and passionate nanny ready to bring joy and care to your family. With a special talent for nurturing infants, I ensure their safety and happiness with gentle, attentive care. My extensive experience with children with special needs has honed my patience, compassion, and adaptability, making me a versatile caregiver.

For older children, I love creating exciting and educational activities that keep them engaged and help them grow. Whether it's a fun art project, a new science experiment, or an adventurous outdoor game, I strive to make every moment enjoyable and meaningful.

Choosing me as your nanny means choosing a safe, inclusive, and nurturing environment for your child. I am committed to providing the highest level of care, giving you peace of mind and your child a wonderful experience.

I can't wait to meet your little ones and be a positive presence in their lives!

description.originalText: Tatyana is an amazing nanny! She was incredibly attentive and stepped in when I needed a last-minute sitter. She has the patience of a saint and took such great care of my child. I highly recommend her to anyone in need of reliable and compassionate babysitter.

bio.experienceSummary: Hi, my name is Krista. I am a certified special education teacher with lots of experience working with children!

I've always cherished my role as a caretaker for children, finding joy in nurturing their development and growth. With three years of experience in childcare, I've honed my skills in providing a safe and nurturing environment for children of various ages. Whether it's engaging in fun activities, helping with homework, or simply lending a listening ear, I strive to make a positive impact on their lives.

My patient, creative, and approachable nature allows me to connect easily with children and build strong relationships with them. I believe in open and transparent communication with parents, ensuring that they're regularly updated about their child's day and any concerns that arise.

I'm well-versed in enforcing household rules and maintaining a structured environment while still allowing room for creativity and fun. From outdoor games and sports to educational games that foster learning, I have a diverse range of activities to keep children entertained and engaged.

Hey, I am a mother of 2 girls and 1 boy and I'm very fun to be with. I have experience in this field taking care of kids through any ages. Also as a senior care taker. I worked for a daycare, for 3 years. I tutor up to 5th grade. I am very reliable, honest and fun. Kids love me and I love them.

description.displayText: Very honest and dependable. I don't have to worry about a thing, Very warm and kind in heart!
description.originalText: Very honest and dependable. I don't have to worry about a thing, Very warm and kind in heart!
